This is a list of messages in ''NetHack'' that begin with "'''You hear'''". If the [[Options#acoustics|<tt>acoustics</tt>]] option is set to FALSE, many of these messages with will not be displayed.

As of [[NetHack 3.6.0]], being [[deaf]] will also cause these message not to display; this can make it difficult to guess the [[passtune]].

==You==
{{message|You hear the howling of the CwnAnnwn...|You have less than {{frac|10}} of your maximum hit points left. (The [[wikipedia:Cŵn Annwn|Cŵn Annwn]] are the hounds of [[wikipedia:Annwn|Annwn]], the underworld from Welsh mythology, whose howls are seen as a death omen.)}}
{{message|You hear the wailing of the Banshee...|You have only 1 hit point left. (The [[wikipedia:Banshee|Banshee]] is a spirit from Irish mythology whose wails can be heard when someone is on the verge of death.)}}

==Monsters==
{{message|You hear some noises <in the distance>.|An unseen monster (typically your [[pet]], or possibly one affected by [[conflict]]) attacked another one.}}
{{message|You hear a <nearby/distant> zap.|An unseen monster zapped a [[wand]].}}
{{message|You hear a chugging sound.|An unseen monster drank a [[potion]].}}
{{message|You hear a monster behind the boulder. Perhaps that's why you cannot move it.|You attempted to push a boulder onto a space already occupied by a monster.}}

===Pets===
{{message|You hear the rumble of distant thunder...|You killed your [[pet]]. You get a &minus;15 penalty to your [[alignment record]] and &minus;1 to [[Luck]].}}
{{message|You hear the studio audience applaud!|As above, while [[hallucinating]].}}

===Werecreatures===
{{message|You hear a <jackal/wolf> howling at the moon.|There is a [[werejackal]] or [[werewolf]] somewhere on the level.}}

===Other monsters===
{{message|You hear a slurping sound.<br>You hear several slurping sounds.|A [[gelatinous cube]] somewhere on the level ate one or more items.}}
{{message|You hear a crunching sound.|A [[metallivore]] somewhere on the level ate a metallic object.}}
{{message|You hear crashing rock.|A [[Dwarf (monster)|dwarf]] or a [[tunneling monster]] somewhere on the level dug through a wall.}}
{{message|You hear something crash through the ground.|An unseen monster went through a [[hole]] in the ground.}}
{{message|You hear a door open.|A monster opened an unseen [[door]].}}
{{message|You hear a door crash open.|A monster bashed through an unseen door.}}
{{message|You hear a door unlock and open.|A monster opened an unseen [[door]] that was locked. [[Shopkeeper]]s and the [[Riders]] might unlock doors, as might a monster carrying a [[skeleton key]] (usually a [[nymph]] who has stolen one).}}
{{message|You hear a blast.|An unseen [[gas spore]] exploded.}}
{{message|You hear a crashing sound.|An unseen door, secret door, or trap door was destroyed.}}
{{message|You hear a rushing noise nearby.|An unseen [[vortex]] or [[air elemental]] attempted to engulf you but attacked the wrong spot.}}
{{message|You hear a splat nearby.|An unseen [[ochre jelly]] or [[Juiblex]] attempted to engulf you but attacked the wrong spot.}}
{{message|You hear a thud.|An unseen monster shrank out of its [[body armor]] as it transformed (through a [[polymorph trap]] or [[lycanthropy]]).}}
{{message|You hear a clank.|An unseen monster dropped its [[shield]] or [[helm]] as it transformed and became headless, horned, or handless.}}
{{message|You hear a cracking sound.|An unseen monster broke out of its body armor as it transformed and became too large or the wrong shape to wear it.}}
{{message|You hear a ripping sound.|An unseen monster tore out of its [[shirt]] or [[cloak]] as it transformed and became too large or the wrong shape to wear it.}}
{{message|You hear chewing.|An unseen monster ate a [[lizard]] corpse or [[acid]]ic corpse to survive [[stoning]].}}
{{message|You hear a cough.|An unseen [[cancellation|canceled]] monster attempted to use its [[breath]], and there was no effect.}}
{{message|You hear an awful gobbling noise.|An unseen [[ghoul]] ate an old corpse.}}
{{message|You hear a faint sloshing sound.|Two [[glob]]s merged on the floor, but you could not see the resulting glob.}}

==Dungeon features==
{{message|You hear a slow drip.}} {{message|You hear a gurgling noise.|There is a [[sink]] on the level.}}
{{message|You hear dishes being washed!|There is a sink on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]].}}
{{message|You hear water falling on coins.}} {{message|You hear the splashing of a naiad.}} {{message|You hear bubbling water.|There is a [[fountain]] on the level. (A [[wikipedia:naiad|naiad]] is a type of nymph in Greek mythology, associated with fountains and other sources of fresh water.)}}
{{message|You hear a soda fountain!|There is a fountain on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]].}}
{{message|You hear <number> tumbler(s) click.|You played a sequence of notes on a musical instrument near the [[castle]]'s [[drawbridge]]. The number is how many notes matched the pitch of notes in the [[passtune]], but did not match the position of those notes within the sequence.}}
{{message|You hear <number> gear(s) turn.|As above, but the number is how many notes matched the pitch <em>and</em> position of notes in the passtune.}}

===Traps===
{{message|You hear rumbling in the distance.|An unseen monster set off a [[rolling boulder trap]].}}
{{message|You hear someone bowling.|An unseen monster set off a rolling boulder trap, and you are [[hallucinating]].}}
{{message|You hear a rumbling stop abruptly.|An unseen boulder rolled onto a [[teleportation trap]].}}
{{message|You hear a loud crash!|An unseen rolling boulder hit another boulder.}}
{{message|You hear a distant explosion.|A monster opened an unseen trapped door.}}
{{message|Kaablamm! You hear an explosion in the distance.|An unseen monster stepped on a [[land mine]].}}
{{message|You hear a distant squeaking sound.|An unseen monster stepped on a [[squeaky board]].}}
{{message|You hear the roaring of a confused bear!|An unseen [[bugbear]] or [[owlbear]] got stuck in a [[web]].}}
{{message|You hear the roaring of an angry bear!|An unseen bugbear or owlbear got stuck in a [[bear trap]].}}
{{message|You hear a deafening roar!|A magic trap you activated summoned monsters in your vicinity. This [[deaf]]ens you.}}
{{message|You hear distant howling.|You stepped on a [[magic trap]]. No effect.}}
{{message|You hear the moon howling at you.|You stepped on a magic trap while [[Hallucination|hallucinating]]. No effect.}}
{{message|You hear a loud click!|An [[arrow trap]] you stepped on was destroyed instead of activating.}}
{{message|You hear a soft click!|A [[dart trap]] you stepped on was destroyed instead of activating.}}
{{message|You hear a twang followed by a thud.|An unseen [[trap door]] was locked.}}

==Special rooms==
{{message|You hear a sound reminiscent of a seal barking.}} {{message|You hear a sound reminiscent of an elephant stepping on a peanut.|There is a [[zoo]] on the level.}}
{{message|You hear Doctor Doolittle!|There is a zoo on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]]. ([[wikipedia:Doctor Dolittle|Doctor Dolittle]] is a fictional doctor who works with animals.)}}

{{message|You hear the footsteps of a guard on patrol.|There is a [[vault]] on the level.}}
{{message|You hear someone counting money.|There is a vault on the level with gold inside.}}
{{message|You hear someone searching.|There is an empty vault on the level.}}
{{message|You hear Ebenezer Scrooge!|There is a vault on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]]. ([[wikipedia:Ebenezer Scrooge|Ebenezer Scrooge]] is the miserly protagonist of [[wikipedia: Charles Dickens|Charles Dickens's]] ''[[wikipedia:A Christmas Carol|A Christmas Carol]]''.)}}
{{message|You hear the quarterback calling the play.|There is a vault on the level with gold inside, and you are hallucinating. (A [[wikipedia:Quarterback|quarterback]] is a position in [[wikipedia:American football|American football]]. When calling a play, a quarterback characteristically lists a series of numbers.)}}

{{message|You hear snoring snakes.<br>You hear a strange wind.<br>You hear convulsive ravings.|[[Oracle (monster)|The Oracle]] is present on [[Oracle (level)|her level]].}}
{{message|You hear someone say "No more woodchucks!"<br>You hear a loud ZOT!|As above while you are hallucinating. (These sounds are a reference to the [http://cgi.cs.indiana.edu/~oracle/index.cgi Internet Oracle].)}}

{{message|You hear the tones of courtly conversation.<br>You hear a sceptre pounded in judgment.<br>Someone shouts "Off with <his/her> head!"|There is a [[throne room]] on the level. The pronoun matches the player's [[gender]]. ("Off with his head!" is famously shouted by the [[wikipedia:Queen of Hearts (Alice's Adventures in Wonderland)|Queen of Hearts]] in [[wikipedia:Lewis Carroll|Lewis Carroll's]] ''[[wikipedia:Alice's Adventures in Wonderland|Alice's Adventures in Wonderland]]''.)}}
{{message|You hear Queen Beruthiel's cats!|There is a throne room on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]]. ([[wikipedia:Queen Berúthiel|Queen Berúthiel]] of Tolkien's works was notorious for her cats.)}}

{{message|You hear someone praising <deity>.<br>You hear someone beseeching <deity>.|There is a [[temple]] to the deity on the level, attended by a coaligned [[aligned priest|priest]] (who is able to speak).{{refsrc|src/sounds.c|241|version=NetHack 3.6.0|comment=Temple sounds}}}}
{{message|You hear an animal carcass being offered in sacrifice.|There is a temple on the level attended by a coaligned priest, and you can't see the priest or altar.}}
{{message|You hear a strident plea for donations.|There is a temple on the level with a coaligned priest who can speak, and you are [[hallucinating]].}}

{{message|You hear a low buzzing.<br>You hear an angry drone.|There is a [[beehive]] on the level.}}
{{message|You hear bees in your bonnet!|As above, while you are hallucinating and wearing a [[helm]].}}
{{message|You hear bees in your (nonexistent) bonnet!|As above, while hallucinating and not wearing a helm.}}

{{message|You suddenly realize it is unnaturally quiet.<br>The <hair> on the back of your <neck> stands up.|There is a [[graveyard]] on the level.}}
{{message|The <hair> on your <head> seems to stand up.|There is a graveyard on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]].}}
{{message|You hear blades being honed.<br>You hear loud snoring.<br>You hear dice being thrown.|There is a [[barracks]] on the level.}}
{{message|You hear General MacArthur!|There is a barracks on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]]. (General of the Army [[wikipedia:Douglas MacArthur|Douglas MacArthur]] was a famous United States Army general and field marshal of the Philippine Army.)}}
{{message|You hear mosquitoes!<br>You smell marsh gas!|There is a [[swamp]] on the level.}}<!--Doesn't match "You hear" format, but does it show up in the file?-->
{{message|You hear Donald Duck!|There is a swamp on the level, and you are [[hallucinating]]. ([[wikipedia:Donald Duck|Donald Duck]] is a Walt Disney cartoon and comic-book character.)}}
{{message|You hear someone cursing shoplifters.<br>You hear the chime of a cash register.|There is a [[shop]] on the level, attended by a [[shopkeeper]].}}
{{message|You hear Neiman and Marcus arguing!|There is a shop on the level attended by a shopkeeper, and you are [[hallucinating]]. ([[wikipedia:Neiman Marcus|Neiman Marcus]] is an upscale department store in the United States.)}}

==Items==
{{message|You hear something shatter!|An unseen [[fragile]] item was destroyed.}}
{{message|You hear a crumbling sound.|An unseen [[boulder]] or [[statue]] was destroyed.}}

===Scroll===
{{message|You hear maniacal laughter close by.|You read a [[scroll of scare monster]], and at least one non-tame monster was [[scare]]d.}}
{{message|You hear maniacal laughter in the distance.|As above, but no non-tame monsters were affected.}}
{{message|You hear sad wailing close by.|You read a scroll of scare monster while [[confused]], or the scroll was [[cursed]], and at least one non-tame monster was awoken, un-paralyzed, or un-scared.}}
{{message|You hear sad wailing in the distance.|As above, but no non-tame monsters were affected.}}

===Container===

{{message|You hear a muffled shatter.|You [[kick]]ed a [[container]] and destroyed a [[fragile]] item inside.}}
{{message|You hear a muffled cracking.|You kicked a container and broke an [[egg]] inside.}}

===Stethoscope===

{{message|You barely hear faint splashing.|You applied a [[stethoscope]] up or down while [[underwater]].}}
{{message|You hear the crackling of hellfire.|You applied a stethoscope to the floor of the [[castle]], beneath which lies the [[Valley of the Dead]].}}
{{message|You hear your heart beat.|You applied a [[cursed]] stethoscope; this has a 50% chance of replacing the normal message.}}
{{message|You hear a faint typing noise.|You applied a stethoscope to the edge of the map.}}
{{message|You hear a hollow sound. This must be a secret <door/passage>!|You applied a stethoscope to a wall concealing a [[secret door]] or [[secret passage]].}}
{{message|You hear a voice say, "It's dead, Jim."|You applied a stethoscope to a [[corpse]] while [[hallucinating]]. (This is a reference to a phrase often uttered by Dr. McCoy in ''[[wikipedia:Star Trek|Star Trek]]'' upon examining or discovering the body of a recently deceased.)}}

===Bugle===
{{message|You hear a bugle playing reveille!|A [[sergeant]], [[lieutenant]], or [[captain]] on the level used a [[bugle]].}}
{{message|You hear the rattle of battle gear being readied.|A [[soldier]] on the level is awakened.}}

==Dungeon environment==
{{message|You hear hissing gas.|An unseen [[moat]] was boiled away by [[fire]].}}
{{message|You hear a soft crackling.|An unseen moat was frozen by a bolt of [[cold]].}}
{{message|You hear a crackling sound.|An unseen square of water on the [[Plane of Water]] was frozen by a bolt of cold.}}

